<h2>Aid</h2>

<p>
  Aid lets you send resources directly to another player as a gift.
  This is useful for helping allies grow or survive difficult situations.
</p>

<h4>Resources You Can Send</h4>
<p>wood, food, iron, gold, tools, maces, swords, bows, horses, wine</p>

<h4>How Aid Works</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Aid is subject to a <strong>5% merchant fee</strong> — the recipient receives 95% of what you send.</li>
  <li>Aid uses your local trade capacity (counts against your max trades for that turn).</li>
  <li>Goods take <strong>3 turns</strong> to arrive.</li>
  <li>You can only send aid to a specific player once every <strong>4 hours</strong>.</li>
</ul>

<div class="alert alert-info">
  <strong>Tip:</strong> Coordinate with alliance members to share resources efficiently.
  Sending iron and tools to a new alliance member helps them build faster.
  Sending food can help an empire survive a food shortage before their farms come online.
</div>

<h4>Canceling Aid</h4>
<p>You can cancel an aid caravan while it is still en route on the Aid tab. The goods will be returned to you.</p>
